Peacock May Sell Bonmarche Clothing Stores, Telegraph Reports

-- B y   N i d a a   B a k h s h
-- 
2011-03-20T10:54:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-20/peacock-may-sell-bonmarche-clothing-stores-telegraph-reports.html
Peacock Group Plc, a U.K. clothing
retailer, may sell its Bonmarche stores that cater to women over
the age of 45, the Sunday Telegraph reported.  Peacock appointed DC Advisory Partners Ltd. to look at
options for the business, the paper reported, without saying
where it got the information. Bonmarche has more than 380 stores
and employs 4,000 people, according to the paper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nidaa Bakhsh in London at 
 nbakhsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  